<div class="content">
    <h1 class="title is-1 ml-2">About This Project</h1>

    <p class="ml-5">
    The data being used in this project is the Pokémon TCG API. I'm using several
    endpoints from this API: <strong>Cards</strong>, <strong>Sets</strong>, 
    <strong>Types</strong>, <strong>Supertypes</strong>, and <strong>Rarities</strong>.
    These data sources are all related because they come from one API.
    </p>

    <h2 class="title is-3 mt-5 ml-2">Tables Used</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Cards</li>
        <li>Sets</li>
        <li>Attacks</li>
        <li>CardAttacks</li>
        <li>PokemonTypes</li>
        <li>Supertypes</li>
        <li>Rarities</li>
        <li>Images</li>
    </ul>

    <p class="mt-4 ml-5">
    In addition to the columns that are automatically provided when
    the models are created, here’s what each table contains:
    </p>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Cards Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the card</li>
        <li><strong>healthpoints</strong> – the total health of the Pokémon</li>
        <li><strong>card_number</strong> – the number of the card in the set</li>
        <li><strong>supertype</strong> – the card's supertype (FK to Supertypes)</li>
        <li><strong>rarity</strong> – the rarity of the card (FK to Rarities)</li>
        <li><strong>pokemon_type</strong> – the type of the Pokémon (FK to PokemonTypes)</li>
        <li><strong>set</strong> – the set the Pokémon card comes from (FK to Sets)</li>
        <li><strong>image_url</strong> – the URL of the Pokémon card image (FK to Images)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Sets Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the set</li>
        <li><strong>release_date</strong> – the date the set was released</li>
        <li><strong>logo</strong> – the logo of the set (FK to Images)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">CardAttacks Table</h3>
    <p class="ml-5">Joiner table between Attacks and Cards (many-to-many relationship):</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>attack_id</strong> – foreign key to Attacks</li>
        <li><strong>card_id</strong> – foreign key to Cards</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Attacks Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the attack</li>
        <li><strong>converted_energy_cost</strong> – total energy required</li>
        <li><strong>damage</strong> – damage done by the attack</li>
        <li><strong>text</strong> – description of what the attack does</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">PokemonTypes Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the type (Fire, Water, etc.)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Supertypes Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the supertype (Energy, Trainer, Pokémon)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Rarities Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>name</strong> – the name of the rarity (Holo, Foil, Ultra Rare, etc.)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="title is-4 mt-4 ml-2">Images Table</h3>
    <ul>
        <li class="mb-5"><strong>image_url</strong> – the URL for the image displayed on the card</li>
    </ul>

    <p><strong class="ml-2">This project's ERD:</strong></p>
    <p class="ml-2"><%= image_tag "ERD.png", alt: "My Project ERD" %></p>
</div>

